<p>We won’t publish reviews that contain threats of public fear, terrorism or threats towards any individual.</p>

<h3 id="copyright">Copyright</h3>

<p>You must own the copyright to any material you include in your review - especially if you’ve copied it from another source. We won’t publish your review if we think you don’t own any part of the content.</p>

<p>Your review will be published to the general public. In submitting your comments you assign all rights to NHS.UK for use and publication of your contribution. You can find more information in our <a href="https://www.nhs.uk/aboutnhschoices/aboutnhschoices/termsandconditions/pages/termsandconditions.aspx">terms and conditions</a>.</p>

<p>You shouldn’t leave a review if you’re not happy to give NHS.UK copyright.</p>

<h3 id="privacy">Privacy</h3>

<p>We will ask you to either create an account or leave a valid email address. We’ll only use your details to contact you about your review. We won’t pass your details to any other party unless permitted or required to by the 1998 Data Protection Act, or
  required to by order of a court.</p>

<h3 id="action-we-might-take">Action we might take</h3>

<p>We can reject your review if you break our rules. Repeated or serious breaches of our rules may lead to blocking contributions from your email address or suspending your account, if you have one.</p>

<p>We reserve the right to delete any content at any time for any reason.</p>

<p>We are not under any obligation to publish any contribution.</p>

<p>We reserve the right to alter or update our rules or terms and conditions at any time.</p>

